originalText.text: I've known Tess for over 15 years, ever since seeking her out to institutionalize and develop the board of an international NGO I founded. She truly is one of the most strategic and insightful people I know. Tess is the smartest person in most rooms she enters, but instead of lording it over you, she's someone who takes your hand and kindly leads you to where her creative mind goes. And where it goes has proven, time and time again, to be a practical, yet audacious, plan that supports the flourishing of an organization.

originalText.text: Tess O’Dwyer has comprehensive knowledge of the field of fund-raising and is a brilliant strategist.  She rather quickly grasps the power structure inherent in any funding challenge and starts creating a roadmap to its solution.  She is the essence of “high energy”, and is capable of considering several levels of information at once to tailor-make actionable steps forward. (I suspect she has never heard of a cookie cutter!) This sophistication makes her particularly valuable to those in high-visibility leadership positions.  She is also a trustworthy confidant. Her qualifications could rightfully make her intimidating, but instead she brings great wit, kindness, and human understanding to all aspects of her work. In working with her on several projects, I found that with Tess O’Dwyer as a partner, no undertaking felt too daunting.

originalText.text: Tess O'Dwyer is a top-notch nonprofit management and fundraising professional. She is an outstanding communicator and strategic thinker. Tess can effectively manage all aspects of project whether it be a campaign, gala benefit or building a new board of trustees. I highly recommend Ms. O'Dwyer for your non-profit management needs.

originalText.text: Tess is a leading mind in this field and a consummate professional. Her years of experience, steady counsel, and innovative thinking around fundraising, organizational design and board building/management have been transformative for The Africa Center during a crucial stage of our transition.
